### Test: Bad Request (400) - Empty Address
### This test validates that empty address strings return 400 Bad Request
POST http://localhost:3000/api/v1/validate-address
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "address": ""
}

### Expected Response (400 Bad Request):
### {
###   "statusCode": 400,
###   "message": [
###     "address should not be empty"
###   ],
###   "error": "Bad Request"
### }

### Test: Bad Request (400) - Missing Address Field
POST http://localhost:3000/api/v1/validate-address
Content-Type: application/json

{}

### Expected Response (400 Bad Request):
### {
###   "statusCode": 400,
###   "message": [
###     "address should not be empty",
###     "address must be a string"
###   ],
###   "error": "Bad Request"
### }

### Test: Bad Request (400) - Non-String Address
POST http://localhost:3000/api/v1/validate-address
Content-Type: application/json

{
  "address": 12345
}

### Expected Response (400 Bad Request):
### {
###   "statusCode": 400,
###   "message": [
###     "address must be a string"
###   ],
###   "error": "Bad Request"
### }

